article.headline: Kansas St. 82, Wagner 53
article.story: MANHATTAN, Kan. -- Dominique Sutton scored a career-high 21 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for his first double-double as Kansas State defeated Wagner 82-53 Tuesday night. Jacob Pullen had 24 points and Denis Clemente 15 for the Wildcats (9-3), while Joey Mundweiler led Wagner (7-4) with 17. Kansas State went 5-for-5 from 3-point range in a 24-2 run to open the game. The Seahawks missed their first 10 shots and did not get a bucket until Jamal Smith's layup with 10:21 remaining in the first period. Mundweiler had seven points in a 14-1 run that closed the deficit to 18 midway through the second half, but Ron Anderson's two free throws ignited a 9-0 run for the Wildcats.
